---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | TinyIMG"
  description="TinyIMG privacy policy — your images never leave your device. No uploads, no tracking, no accounts."
>
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-10">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3">Your images never leave your device</h2>
        <p>
          TinyIMG processes all images <span class="text-white font-medium">100% client-side</span> in your browser.
          No image data is ever uploaded to any server. Compression, conversion, resizing, editing, and background
          removal all happen locally using Web Workers and the browser's built-in graphics APIs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3">No data collection</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside marker:text-gold/50">
          <li>No cookies are set by TinyIMG.</li>
          <li>No analytics or tracking scripts are loaded.</li>
          <li>No account or sign-up is required.</li>
          <li>No personal information is collected or stored.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3">Local storage and IndexedDB</h2>
        <p>
          TinyIMG uses <span class="text-white font-medium">IndexedDB</span> solely to transfer images between tools
          on the same device (for example, sending an image from the compressor to the editor). This data is
          temporary and is cleared automatically as soon as the receiving tool reads it. Nothing is persisted
          beyond the active session.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3">Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          TinyIMG is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may collect standard web server access logs
          (IP address, browser type, pages visited) as described in the
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gold hover:text-gold-light underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a>.
          TinyIMG itself does not have access to these logs.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Google Fonts are loaded from Google's servers to render the Inter and DM Serif Display typefaces.
          Google may log font requests per its
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gold hover:text-gold-light underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes, the updated date at the top of this page will reflect that. We will never
          introduce user tracking or data collection without a clear, prominent notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about privacy? Open an issue or discussion on the project repository.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
